headline: Is Tractor Supply’s Recent 7.3% Dip a Buying Opportunity for 2025?
summary: Trying to decide what to do with Tractor Supply stock? You are not alone. Whether you are holding, buying, or just watching from the sidelines, TSCO has given investors a lot to think about lately. The past year has not been a smooth ride, as shares are down 3.6% over 12 months, and the last month alone saw a 7.3% dip. Even so, if you zoom out, the longer-term picture still looks robust, with a remarkable 123.3% gain over the past five years. So, is the recent weakness just noise, or is it...
